parameters:
Director Staro: I have been taken care of by Agonia-san.
The crystal you requested is inside this box.

Thief Nora: W-Wow, this is an amazing place. It seems safe
even if a dragon were to come.

Director Staro: Some people even say that this place is
like a fortress, although it might be impossible for a
dragon to get in.

Mage Relm: Considering the high value of the crystal, I
think it's only natural to take precautions for its
management.

Director Staro: If only we hadn't had that one failure,
this impregnable crystal warehouse...

Director Staro: It was the infamous thief Perno... Only
that person was able to infiltrate and steal from us!

Director Staro: And on top of that, they had the audacity
to infiltrate without even touching the crystal, boasting
about it as if it were something trivial!

Swift Celis: I heard that we can also borrow a carriage on
another occasion.

Director Staro: Oh, excuse me! I have prepared a sturdy
carriage for you.
Director Staro: Please give my regards to Lady Kasaro.

Swift Celis: This mission is a race against time. The key
to victory is how quickly we can navigate through this
dangerous place.

Swift Celis: So when you're ready to go without taking a
break, talk to me.

Celis, the Gale: Everyone, get on the carriage and let's
dash through to a safe place with certainty.
Celis, the Gale: Let me know when you're ready.

Veteran Worker: There's a lot of cargo today! Make sure you
don't make any mistakes with the delivery destination!

Novice Worker: It's really dizzying how busy we are,
sending them all over the empire...

Male Deliveryman: Lately, there has been an increase in
thieves. After a war like this, the public order tends to
deteriorate.
Phantom Thief Perno: Hehe, you look curious, don't you?

Clea: Even though I was being watched, why didn't anyone
notice?

Phantom Thief Perno: Because I'm using magic to conceal my
presence, no one can notice that I exist.

Phantom Thief Perno: However, it doesn't work on types with
instincts like wild animals.

Phantom Thief Perno: I did feel a strange presence... It's
probably better to assume that someone is already inside.
Phantom Thief Perno: Hahaha, it's hunting time!

Phantom Thief Perno: Indeed, that type of person. Let's
proceed cautiously to the top floor from here.
Phantom Thief Perno: ...Now, our night has come.
